PROMS Installation Instructions
-------------------------------

* Copy the installation to the destination machine and change to the installation directory.

* Change the permissions for the installation scripts to allow execution, e.g:

sudo chmod -R +x ./

* Run the installation script.

sudo ./install.bash

* Change to the PROMS directory:

cd /opt/proms

* Modify the necessary settings in the file settings.py. by changing the base server URIs to match your server name
  or URI. E.g:

# Replace "localhost" with your server name or IP address
PROMS_INSTANCE_NAMESPACE_URI = 'http://localhost/'
FUSEKI_QUERY_URI = 'http://localhost/fuseki/data/query'
FUSEKI_UPDATE_URI = 'http://localhost/fuseki/data/update'
FUSEKI_SECURE_QUERY_URI = 'http://localhost/fuseki/data/query'
FUSEKI_SECURE_UPDATE_URI = 'http://localhost/fuseki/data/update'

* Run PROMS (while still in the /opt/proms directory):

sudo ./start.bash

* Report any problems to nick.car@csiro.au
